      <section eId="sec_CHC-1112">
        <num>CHC 1112</num>
        <heading>1112. Â Inability due to court intervention</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1112__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as provided herein, a parent may not execute a private surrender once custody of that child has been removed from the parent by order of a juvenile court and the child has been placed in the legal custody of any person or agency or if the child is the subject of a pending termination of parental rights proceeding.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1112__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Upon notice to the department and after a contradictory hearing, if requested by the department, a parent may, with approval of the court, execute a private surrender of a child in the legal custody of the department to the foster parent with whom the child was placed by the department.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72596</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
